text.section:
The court may not commit a child to the custody of the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene under this section for inpatient care and treatment in a State mental hospital unless the court finds on the record based upon clear and convincing evidence that:
The child has a mental disorder;
The child needs inpatient medical care or treatment for the protection of himself or others;
The child is unable or unwilling to be voluntarily admitted to such facility; and
There is no less restrictive form of intervention available which is consistent with the child's condition and welfare.
